verses.text_plain: And when Balaam saw that it pleased the Lord to bless Israel, he went not, as at other times, to seek for enchantments, but he set his face toward the wilderness.
verses.verse_html:
1And when Balaam saw that it pleased the Lord to bless Israel, he went not, as at other times, to seek for enchantments, but he set his face toward the wilderness. ▼
▼ to seek…: Heb. to the meeting of

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to seek…: Heb. to the meeting of
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to seek…: Heb. to the meeting of

verses.text_plain: And Balaam lifted up his eyes, and he saw Israel abiding in his tents according to their tribes; and the spirit of God came upon him.
verses.verse_html: 2And Balaam lifted up his eyes, and he saw Israel abiding in his tents according to their tribes; and the spirit of God came upon him.

verses.text_plain: And he took up his parable, and said, Balaam the son of Beor hath said, and the man whose eyes are open hath said:
verses.verse_html:
3And he took up his parable, and said, Balaam the son of Beor hath said, and the man whose eyes are open hath said: ▼
▼ whose…: Heb. who had his eyes shut, but now opened

footnotes.body_text: ▼ whose…: Heb. who had his eyes shut, but now opened
footnotes.body_html: ▼ whose…: Heb. who had his eyes shut, but now opened

verses.text_plain: He hath said, which heard the words of God, which saw the vision of the Almighty, falling into a trance, but having his eyes open:
verses.verse_html: 4He hath said, which heard the words of God, which saw the vision of the Almighty, falling into a trance, but having his eyes open:

verses.text_plain: How goodly are thy tents, O Jacob, and thy tabernacles, O Israel!
verses.verse_html: 5How goodly are thy tents, O Jacob, and thy tabernacles, O Israel!

verses.text_plain: As the valleys are they spread forth, as gardens by the river’s side, as the trees of lign aloes which the Lord hath planted, and as cedar trees beside the waters.
verses.verse_html: 6As the valleys are they spread forth, as gardens by the river’s side, as the trees of lign aloes which the Lord hath planted, and as cedar trees beside the waters.

tokens.text: as the trees of lign aloes

verses.text_plain: He shall pour the water out of his buckets, and his seed shall be in many waters, and his king shall be higher than Agag, and his kingdom shall be exalted.
verses.verse_html: 7He shall pour the water out of his buckets, and his seed shall be in many waters, and his king shall be higher than Agag, and his kingdom shall be exalted.

verses.text_plain: God brought him forth out of Egypt; he hath as it were the strength of an unicorn: he shall eat up the nations his enemies, and shall break their bones, and pierce them through with his arrows.
verses.verse_html: 8God brought him forth out of Egypt; he hath as it were the strength of an unicorn: he shall eat up the nations his enemies, and shall break their bones, and pierce them through with his arrows.

tokens.text: he hath as it were the strength

verses.text_plain: He couched, he lay down as a lion, and as a great lion: who shall stir him up? Blessed is he that blesseth thee, and cursed is he that curseth thee.
verses.verse_html: 9He couched, he lay down as a lion, and as a great lion: who shall stir him up? Blessed is he that blesseth thee, and cursed is he that curseth thee.

verses.text_plain: And Balak’s anger was kindled against Balaam, and he smote his hands together: and Balak said unto Balaam, I called thee to curse mine enemies, and, behold, thou hast altogether blessed them these three times.
verses.verse_html: 10And Balak’s anger was kindled against Balaam, and he smote his hands together: and Balak said unto Balaam, I called thee to curse mine enemies, and, behold, thou hast altogether blessed them these three times.

verses.text_plain: Therefore now flee thou to thy place: I thought to promote thee unto great honour; but, lo, the Lord hath kept thee back from honour.
verses.verse_html: 11Therefore now flee thou to thy place: I thought to promote thee unto great honour; but, lo, the Lord hath kept thee back from honour.

verses.text_plain: And Balaam said unto Balak, Spake I not also to thy messengers which thou sentest unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 12And Balaam said unto Balak, Spake I not also to thy messengers which thou sentest unto me, saying,

tokens.text: I not also to thy messengers

verses.text_plain: If Balak would give me his house full of silver and gold, I cannot go beyond the commandment of the Lord, to do either good or bad of mine own mind; but what the Lord saith, that will I speak?
verses.verse_html: 13If Balak would give me his house full of silver and gold, I cannot go beyond the commandment of the Lord, to do either good or bad of mine own mind; but what the Lord saith, that will I speak?

verses.text_plain: And now, behold, I go unto my people: come therefore, and I will advertise thee what this people shall do to thy people in the latter days.
verses.verse_html: 14And now, behold, I go unto my people: come therefore, and I will advertise thee what this people shall do to thy people in the latter days.

verses.text_plain: And he took up his parable, and said, Balaam the son of Beor hath said, and the man whose eyes are open hath said:
verses.verse_html: 15And he took up his parable, and said, Balaam the son of Beor hath said, and the man whose eyes are open hath said:

verses.text_plain: He hath said, which heard the words of God, and knew the knowledge of the most High, which saw the vision of the Almighty, falling into a trance, but having his eyes open:
verses.verse_html: 16He hath said, which heard the words of God, and knew the knowledge of the most High, which saw the vision of the Almighty, falling into a trance, but having his eyes open:

verses.text_plain: I shall see him, but not now: I shall behold him, but not nigh: there shall come a Star out of Jacob, and a Sceptre shall rise out of Israel, and shall smite the corners of Moab, and destroy all the children of Sheth.
verses.verse_html:
17I shall see him, but not now: I shall behold him, but not nigh: there shall come a Star out of Jacob, and a Sceptre shall rise out of Israel, and shall smite the corners of Moab, and destroy all the children of Sheth. ▼
▼ smite…: or, smite through the princes of

tokens.text: him, but not now: I shall behold

footnotes.body_text: ▼ smite…: or, smite through the princes of
footnotes.body_html: ▼ smite…: or, smite through the princes of

verses.text_plain: And Edom shall be a possession, Seir also shall be a possession for his enemies; and Israel shall do valiantly.
verses.verse_html: 18And Edom shall be a possession, Seir also shall be a possession for his enemies; and Israel shall do valiantly.

verses.text_plain: Out of Jacob shall come he that shall have dominion, and shall destroy him that remaineth of the city.
verses.verse_html: 19Out of Jacob shall come he that shall have dominion, and shall destroy him that remaineth of the city.

tokens.text: shall come he that shall have dominion

verses.text_plain: And when he looked on Amalek, he took up his parable, and said, Amalek was the first of the nations; but his latter end shall be that he perish for ever.
verses.verse_html:
20And when he looked on Amalek, he took up his parable, and said, Amalek was the first of the nations; but his latter end shall be that he perish for ever. ▼
▼ the nations: the nations that warred against Israel
 , ▼
▼ that…: or, even to destruction

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the nations: the nations that warred against Israel
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the nations: the nations that warred against Israel
▼ that…: or, even to destruction

verses.text_plain: And he looked on the Kenites, and took up his parable, and said, Strong is thy dwellingplace, and thou puttest thy nest in a rock.
verses.verse_html: 21And he looked on the Kenites, and took up his parable, and said, Strong is thy dwellingplace, and thou puttest thy nest in a rock.

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless the Kenite shall be wasted, until Asshur shall carry thee away captive.
verses.verse_html:
22Nevertheless the Kenite shall be wasted, until Asshur shall carry thee away captive. ▼
▼ the Kenite: Heb. Kain
 , ▼
▼ until…: or, how long shall it be ere Asshur carry thee away captive

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the Kenite: Heb. Kain

footnotes.body_text: ▼ until…: or, how long shall it be ere Asshur carry thee away captive
footnotes.body_html: ▼ until…: or, how long shall it be ere Asshur carry thee away captive

verses.text_plain: And he took up his parable, and said, Alas, who shall live when God doeth this!
verses.verse_html: 23And he took up his parable, and said, Alas, who shall live when God doeth this!

verses.text_plain: And ships shall come from the coast of Chittim, and shall afflict Asshur, and shall afflict Eber, and he also shall perish for ever.
verses.verse_html: 24And ships shall come from the coast of Chittim, and shall afflict Asshur, and shall afflict Eber, and he also shall perish for ever.

verses.text_plain: And Balaam rose up, and went and returned to his place: and Balak also went his way.
verses.verse_html: 25And Balaam rose up, and went and returned to his place: and Balak also went his way.
